Instructions
for
preparing
clay
,
drying
,
glazing
and
firing
are
not
given
.

Glazes
,
one-stroke
ceramic
colors
,
stains
,
cones
as
indicated
in
the
individual
instructions
.

Roll
clay
to
thickness
indicated
in
individual
instructions
.

When
mold
has
more
than
one
design
cavity
,
make
individual
paper
patterns
.

Check
thickness
of
clay
and
build
up
thin
areas
by
moistening
surface
with
a
little
water
and
adding
small
pieces
of
clay
.

This
will
prevent
the
clay
from
twisting
or
bending
,
causing
warping
when
fired
.

If
clay
is
slightly
out
of
shape
,
square
straight
sides
with
guide
sticks
or
rulers
pressed
against
opposite
sides
,
or
smooth
round
pieces
with
damp
fingers
.

(
opposite
