frames
.

The
second
two
pieces
lap
over
the
inner
member
of
the
keelson
and
butt
against
the
outer
member
.

They
are
glued
and
screwed
to
the
inner
member
of
the
keelson
.

The
side
ones
are
a
half-inch
narrower
.

The
chines
go
in
the
same
way
except
that
they
are
made
of
two
pieces
of
two-inch
wood
for
strength
and
easier
