at
all
.

The
fixed
window
panels
with
louvers
should
have
a
good
grade
of
double-strength
glass
set
in
a
mastic
glazing
compound
.

Other
thicknesses
may
necessitate
ripping
a
special
size
lumber
for
the
glass
trim
.

The
drill
press
consists
of
a
vertical
shaft
(
spindle
)
which
is
tapered
or
threaded
on
one
end
to
hold
a
drill
chuck
,
a
tubular
housing
(
quill
)
in
which
the
spindle
is
mounted
,
a
head
in
which
the
quill
is
mounted
,
a
feed
lever
which
moves
the
quill
up
or
down
,
a
power
source
,
and
a
movable
table
upon
which
the
work
is
placed
.

A
new
radial
drill
press
with
a
16
inch
capacity
has
a
tilting
head
that
allows
drilling
to
be
done
at
any
angle
.

The
drill
press
should
be
leveled
and
,
depending
on
whether
it
is
a
bench
or
floor
model
,
bolted
securely
to
a
sturdy
bench
or
stand
or
screwed
to
the
floor
with
lag
or
expansion
screws
.

A
coat
of
paste
wax
or
a
rubdown
with
a
piece
of
wax
paper
will
protect
the
polished
surface
of
the
table
;
;

The
rest
of
the
press
should
be
kept
clean
by
dusting
with
a
clean
rag
or
brush
.

Most
drill
presses
have
a
quill
return
spring
that
raises
the
spindle
automatically
when
the
feed
lever
is
released
and
holds
the
quill
in
the
raised
position
.

Turning
the
housing
clockwise
will
reduce
tension
,
counter-clockwise
will
increase
it
.

Don't
lose
the
chuck
key

Drill
speeds
are
important
if
you
want
a
good
job
.

Feed
pressure
is
also
of
major
importance
.

Too
much
pressure
will
force
the
tool
beyond
its
cutting
capacity
and
result
in
rough
cuts
and
jammed
or
broken
tools
.

The
best
results
will
be
obtained
by
matching
the
correct
speed
with
a
steady
feed
pressure
that
lets
the
tool
cut
easily
at
an
even
rate
.

Fly
cutters
can
fool
you
into
putting
your
hand
too
close
to
the
tool
,
so
if
you
want
to
avoid
nicked
fingers
,
keep
your
hands
well
out
of
the
way
.

The
depth
gauge
rod
can
now
be
set
,
and
any
number
of
holes
bored
to
exact
and
identical
depth
.

The
whole
length
