to
applicants
who
ordinarily
would
not
undertake
the
exploration
under
present
conditions
or
circumstances
at
their
sole
expense
and
who
are
unable
to
obtain
funds
from
commercial
sources
on
reasonable
terms
.

Funds
contributed
by
the
Government
are
repaid
by
a
royalty
on
production
from
the
property
.

If
nothing
is
produced
,
there
is
no
obligation
to
repay
.

The
royalty
applies
to
both
principal
and
interest
,
but
it
never
exceeds
5
percent
.

Only
