because
of
the
still
greater
distance
over
which
these
skywave
signals
may
cause
interference
to
the
signals
of
stations
on
the
same
and
closely
adjacent
frequencies
.

during
the
same
period
around
sunrise
,
skywave
transmission
is
declining
,
until
at
about
2
hours
after
sunrise
it
reaches
a
point
where
it
becomes
of
little
