In
the
Midwest
,
oxidation
ponds
are
used
extensively
for
the
treatment
of
domestic
sewage
from
suburban
areas
.

They
indicated
that
a
4-day
retention
,
aerated
lagoon
would
give
60
to
76
per
cent
BOD
reduction
.

Later
,
Eckenfelder
increased
the
efficiency
of
treatment
to
between
75
and
85
per
cent
in
the
summer
months
.

The
sewage
system
from
Kansas
City
was
not
expected
to
serve
the
Red
Bridge
area
for
several
years
.

For
the
initial
development
an
oxidation
pond
was
constructed
as
shown
in
Figure
1
.

The
oxidation
pond
has
a
surface
area
of
4.77
acres
and
a
depth
of
4
Aj
.

It
was
possible
to
