in
the
pond
by
regular
additions
of
sodium
nitrate
until
the
temperature
decreased
and
the
algae
population
changed
from
blue-green
to
green
algae
.

The
sewage
flow
into
the
treatment
plant
was
metered
and
continuously
recorded
on
24-hr.
charts
.

The
effluent
was
collected
through
two
pipes
and
discharged
to
the
Blue
River
through
a
surface
drainage
ditch
.

Composite
samples
were
collected
at
weekly
intervals
.

The
BOD
of
the
influent
to
the
pilot
plant
varied
between
110
and
710
with
an
average
of
350
Aj
.

The
BOD
of
the
raw
sewage
was
typical
of
domestic
sewage
from
a
subdivision
.

Examination
of
the
data
in
Table
1
,
shows
that
a
few
samples
contributed
to
raising
the
effluent
Aj
.

Ice
caused
the
aerator
to
overload
,
straining
the
drive
belts
.

It
seems
that
the
aerated
lagoon
was
a
very
heavily
loaded
oxidation
pond
or
a
lightly
